commitResults.messageTitle: Level 0. Rename, Greet, Exit: Give your chatbot a new name, Implement an initial skeletal version
Level 1. Echo: echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types the command bye
Level 2. Add, List Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.
Level 3. Mark as Done Add the ability to mark tasks as done. Optionally, add the ability to change the status back to not done.

Level 4. ToDos, Events, Deadlines Add support for tracking three types of tasks: ToDos: tasks without any date/time attached to it Deadlines: tasks that need to be done before a specific date/time Events: tasks that start at a specific date/time and ends at a specific date/time
Test using the I/O redirection technique
Level 5. Handle Errors Teach the chatbot to deal with errors such as incorrect inputs entered by the user.
Level 6. Delete Add support for deleting tasks from the list.

Level 7. Save Save the tasks in the hard disk automatically whenever the task list changes. Load the data from the hard disk when the chatbot starts up. You may hard-code the file name and relative path from the project root e.g., ./data/duke.txt Your code must handle the case where the data file doesn't exist at the start. Stretch goal: Handle the situation of the data file being corrupted (i.e., content not in the expected format).
